title: Facebook investment in hardware could be 'game changer,' trader bets
text: After Facebook's earnings, Todd Gordon of TradingAnalysis.com sees massive growth potential in one of the company's investments.

title: Why Facebook is considering an antitrust lawsuit against Apple
text: Facebook Inc. and Apple Inc. are edging perilously close to all-out legal war, with the social-media giant strongly considering a lawsuit that could ultimately sway antitrust investigators.

title: EU lawmakers, Amazon, Apple, Facebook, Google hearing pushed back by 2 months
text: EU lawmakers, who are gearing up to curb the power of U.S. tech giants, have told Amazon, Apple, Facebook and Alphabet that they are willing to push back a proposed Feb. 1 hearing by two months.

title: Better Buy: Apple vs. Facebook
text: Will the iPhone maker outperform the world's top social network again this year?

title: Facebook Delivers Yet Another Strong Quarter
text: Facebook, Inc. (NASDAQ:FB) is a classic example of a company that continues to beat Wall Street expectations consistently. On Jan 27, the social media giant reported fourth-quarter 2020 earnings per share of $3.88, beating the Wall Street estimate of $3.24.

title: Facebook is working on tools to keep ads away from topics like crime or politics in News Feed
text: Facebook is building tools to help advertisers keep their ad placements away from certain topics in its News Feed.

title: Analysts Boost Price Targets on 4 Top-Large Cap Technology Winners
text: The fourth-quarter earnings results have been pouring in this week, and one thing's for sure.

title: WhatsApp is adding eye, fingerprint, and face scanning – but says it won't have any access to biometric data
text: WhatsApp is adding features to its web app to let users sign by scanning their face, thumbprint, or eye. WhatsApp announced the new feature on Thursday, which it described as an extra layer of security for its WhatsApp Web and Desktop services.

title: Stock Frenzy Fallout: Google Cracks Down On Robinhood ‘Review-Bombing', Facebook Bans Popular Trading Group
text: Angry users had flooded Robinhood's app with negative reviews after the platform decided to curb the trading of Gamestop and other popular stocks.

title: Tim Cook took a swipe at Facebook after Mark Zuckerberg accused Apple of misleading users
text: Apple's privacy war with Facebook is escalating again. CEO Tim Cook launched an attack on business models that prioritize engagement above all and hoover up user data to target users with advertising in a speech to the European Computers, Privacy and Data Protection Conference on Thursday.

title: Facebook's 'supreme court' just ruled against Facebook
text: Facebook's court-like Oversight Board overturned several of the company's decisions to remove content in its first set of decisions since the independent body began hearing cases last fall.

title: Facebook Takes Down Trading Group With 157,000 Members Amid GameStop Frenzy
text: Facebook Inc (NASDAQ: FB) disabled a 157,000-member trading discussion group on its platform that discussed shares of companies like GameStop Corporation (NYSE: GME) and others, Reuters reported Thursday. What Happened: The group — Robinhood Stock Traders — was created by Allen Tran, a 23-year old who was notified by the social network giant that it had been taken down for violating policies on “adult sexual exploitation,” according to Reuters.

title: Facebook is working on a newsletter tool for freelancers and independent writers, The New York Times reports
text: Facebook is gearing up to be a major player in the newsletter subscription service world, according to The New York Times. Three sources familiar with the company's move told The Times that the social media company planned to plunge into a burgeoning space currently dominated by platforms like Substack around the summer.
